post_cb({"6939059": {"ParentId": "6939020", "CommentCount": "4", "Body": "<p>Local classes cannot have static data members in C++.</p>\n<p>To quote the standard (Paragraph 9.8.4)</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_6939020_6939059_0\">A local class shall not have static data members.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>In the unlikely case that you don't know, a local class is a class, struct, or union defined in function scope.</p>\n<p>9.8.1</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_6939020_6939059_1\">A class can be defined within a function definition; such a class is\n  called a local class.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "OwnerUserId": "469935", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "6939059", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2011-08-04T09:31:19.833", "LastActivityDate": "2011-08-04T09:31:19.833"}, "6939079": {"ParentId": "6939020", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p><code>static</code> is a storage class, so it does not properly apply to a <code>typedef</code>.  It's along the same lines as <code>register</code> and <code>const</code>. </p>\n<p>Even if <code>static</code> worked, how would <code>w</code> be static and <code>p</code> not be static?</p>\n<p>This will work though:</p>\n<pre><code>int main()\n{\n    typedef struct a\n    {\n        int w;\n        char *p;\n    } a;\n    static a a0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "198536", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "6939079", "Score": "-1", "CreationDate": "2011-08-04T09:32:55.800", "LastActivityDate": "2011-08-04T09:32:55.800"}, "6939020": {"CommentCount": "0", "ViewCount": "3213", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "469935", "CreationDate": "2011-08-04T09:28:04.307", "LastActivityDate": "2011-08-04T09:32:55.800", "Title": "Compiler Error: \"expected specifier-qualifier-list\"", "AcceptedAnswerId": "6939059", "LastEditDate": "2011-08-04T09:31:35.870", "Id": "6939020", "Score": "1", "Body": "<pre><code>int main()\n{\n    typedef struct a\n    {\n        static int w;\n        char *p;\n    } a;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>on compiling it gives <code> error:expected specifier-qualifier-list before 'static'</code>\ncould u please tell me what this error means and how to remove it?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "665884", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_6939020_6939059_1": {"section_id": 5929, "quality": 0.9090909090909091, "length": 10}, "so_6939020_6939059_0": {"section_id": 5910, "quality": 1.0, "length": 6}}, "n3337": {"so_6939020_6939059_1": {"section_id": 5701, "quality": 0.9090909090909091, "length": 10}, "so_6939020_6939059_0": {"section_id": 5682, "quality": 1.0, "length": 6}}, "n4659": {"so_6939020_6939059_1": {"section_id": 7414, "quality": 0.9090909090909091, "length": 10}, "so_6939020_6939059_0": {"section_id": 7392, "quality": 1.0, "length": 6}}}});